name: methionine gamma-lyase
classes: Carbon-sulfur lyases (only sub-subclass identified to date)
reaction: L-methionine + H2O = methanethiol + NH3 + 2-oxobutanoate (overall reaction) [RN:R00654]; (1a) L-methionine = methanethiol + 2-aminobut-2-enoate [RN:R08635]; (1b) 2-aminobut-2-enoate = 2-iminobutanoate (spontaneous); (1c) 2-iminobutanoate + H2O = 2-oxobutanoate + NH3 (spontaneous)
comment: A pyridoxal-phosphate protein. The enzyme cleaves a carbon-sulfur bond, releasing methanethiol and an unstable enamine product that tautomerizes to an imine form, which undergoes a hydrolytic deamination to form 2-oxobutanoate and ammonia. The latter reaction, which can occur spontaneously, can also be catalysed by EC 3.5.99.10, 2-iminobutanoate/2-iminopropanoate deaminase. The enzyme is involved in L-methionine catabolism.

references.title: Isolation and purification of L-methionine-alpha-deamino-gamma-mercaptomethane-lyase (L-methioninase) from Clostridium sporogenes.
